&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the job:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you graduating soon or looking to start your career in engineering, manufacturing, or digital transformation? Do you enjoy solving analytical challenges and have an interest in product cost management, manufacturing processes, and value engineering? Then CLEVR might have the perfect opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a PCM Consultant to join our team in Stockholm. In this role, you will learn how organizations optimize product costs and improve manufacturing decisions using Siemens Teamcenter Product Cost Management (PCM). Working alongside experienced consultants, you will support customer projects, perform analyses, and gradually develop into a trusted consultant for our customers in optimizing product costs and manufacturing processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&#39;s Build Tomorrow Together!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes this role unique:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of an experienced team working with leading Siemens technology and some of the world&#39;s most innovative manufacturing companies. You will learn how leading manufacturers use cost engineering and value engineering methodologies to make better product development and sourcing decisions. From day one, you will receive training, mentorship, and hands-on project experience to help you develop both your technical and consulting skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As you grow in the role, you will gain exposure to cost engineering, value engineering, manufacturing processes, and digital transformation projects across multiple industries. Working closely with customers, you will support solution demonstrations, advisory activities, and Teamcenter PCM implementations. Ready to take on the challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your role will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting senior consultants during customer projects, including Teamcenter PCM configuration and implementation activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with customer workshops, solution presentations, demonstrations, and training activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with customers to understand business processes related to product costing and manufacturing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparing analyses, reports, presentations, and project documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying opportunities to expand PCM usage and deliver additional value to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver successful project outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously developing your knowledge of Siemens Teamcenter PCM and related digital manufacturing solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
